title: My Travels
name: My Travels
description:
A Map by Kwilli74

The various places I have visited.

properties.name: Albany, NY
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74Albany, NYWhat a small town to be the capital of New York. I cannot believe how dirty this city seems to be. I came here because my wife was born in NY and had to get a birth certificate. You just wouldn\'t believe how difficult it is to get a birth certicate from New York after Sept. 11.

properties.name: Atlanta, GA
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74Atlanta, GAI have been here more times than I can remember. I have been to trade shows here, I have flown out of the ATL airport, I have friends who live here, and I have just come for a little culture. This is a great city depending on what part of the city you end up in.

properties.name: Cancun, Mexico
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74Cancun, MexicoI spent my honeymoon here. This place is gorgeous and everything is dirt cheap. I just hope that the storms in the past few years haven\'t destroyed the beauty. There was snorkling, beer, parasailing, beer, shopping, and tequila

properties.name: Charleston, WV
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74Charleston, WVThis is the worst town I have ever been too. This unfortunately was a city in my territory when I was the account manager for a stone and glass company. This is by far one of the smallest cities I have ever been to. If this were longer than a day and a half trip I would have turned into an alcoholic.

properties.name: Houston, TX
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74Houston, TXWhen I was in sales, my largest customer was based in Houston. A co-worker and I flew to Houston on a business trip.

properties.name: Kansas City, MO
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli746500 N Cosby Ave Kansas City, MO I went to a trade show in Kansas City. The barbecue was phenomenal.

properties.name: Lafayette, IN
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74Lafayette, INI haven\'t been here since I was 10 years old but my Aunt and Uncle live here. This is were I learned to ride a bike and nearly killed myself while trying.

properties.name: Lexington, KY
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli741800 Newtown Pike, Lexington, KY, 40511, USAnother one of my favorite stops as a salesman. If I were into rural settings, Lexington would be great. This city was gorgeous. I was lucky enough to see some serious thoroughbred horses, not that it would be hard to find here.

properties.name: Louisville, KY
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74Louisville KY 40202I have only been to Louisville once. This has to be the worst city I have ever been to. It was in my territory when I was in sales, but I despised this city so much I only went once.

properties.name: Memphis, TN
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74191 Beale Street, Memphis, TNThis was part of my territory when I was the account manager of a stone and glass company. The city wasn\'t what I expected at all, but I did get to see the Pyramid and Graceland.

properties.name: Nashville, TN
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli747648 Highway 70 S, Nashville, TNThis was another one of my favorite cities when I was the account manager of a stone and glass company. When I needed a quick sale, I always came to Nashville.

properties.name: New York City, NY
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74E. 62ndThis is the greatest city in the world. I have been here a few times since my wife\'s family and friends all live in either NY or CT. If I didn\'t have children, I would move here instantly. You must try a hotdog!

properties.name: Orlando, FL
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli748738 International Drive, Orlando, FLI have been to Orlando for multiple reasons. Natually I have been here on vacation, but also for several trade shows when I was a salesman.

properties.name: Panama City Bch., FL
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74Panama City Beach, FLI have a good friend who lives here. I have been here for several Spring Breaks. I don\'t really remember everything about these visits but I am told I had fun.

properties.name: Washington D.C.
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74Washington DC 20008I joined my brother and his friends on a trip to D.C. a few years ago. There was some Christian congregation called "Stand In The Gap" where we all met between he monuments and listened to a lot of sermons and preaching. I was lucky enough to get to see some of the monuments and the museum, although I couldn\'t sneak off as long as I wanted to fully enjoy the culture.

properties.name: Waterbury, CT
properties.description: Posted by Kwilli74Waterbury, CTI spent Christmas 2003 here. My sister-in-law lives here. This is the best of both worlds, big city meets rural. The only drawback is he cost of living.
